race.comment: KEEP ON RUNNING (6) has hit a bit of form at the past couple of efforts and gets in well at the weights with the 3kg claim. Is a three-time winner here and should play a major role in the finish. HOT PURSUIT (7) will be ready to peak now fourth run back from a spell and is sure to get a cosy run in transit from gate five. Right in this contest. The well-related TRAPASSI (3) (half to G1 winner Beiwacht) is yet to miss a drum in three starts over this distance range and is usually about the money. Shapes as one to consider. HOLY CROWN (12) is knocking on the door of another victory with three consecutive placings and looks a must for the multiples. LET'S RIDE (13) makes some appeal despite the wide draw.
